 I'll leave it at the door. 

27
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:23,150
Excuse me, hold on.

28
00:02:23,150 --> 00:02:24,750
- What? 
 - Please help.

29
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:26,890
There's a weird guy inside.

30
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:30,330
You should call the police.

31
00:02:30,330 --> 00:02:32,850
I'm a delivery man.

32
00:02:40,420 --> 00:02:42,580
Is he hiding in the bathroom?

33
00:02:42,580 --> 00:02:44,260
No, he's right in front of us.

34
00:02:44,260 --> 00:02:46,960
- W-Where? 
 - Here. This person.

35
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:50,900
What? What person?

36
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:54,130
He can't see me. Don't waste your time.

37
00:02:54,130 --> 00:02:57,810
- Aigoo. He has a long life left. 
 - What's there?

38
00:02:57,810 --> 00:03:00,030
Thanks for your hard work. You'll live long.

39
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:01,630
You can't hear that either?

40
00:03:01,630 --> 00:03:03,580
Hear what?

41
00:03:09,540 --> 00:03:11,240
- I'm so busy I'm dying. 
 - You won't die.

42
00:03:11,240 --> 00:03:14,080
No, that's not it... I'm sorry.

43
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,270
Whatever. Whatever.

44
00:03:15,270 --> 00:03:18,080
They think delivery men are a joke.

45
00:03:19,670 --> 00:03:22,110
Hello? I'd like to talk to the doctor.

46
00:03:22,110 --> 00:03:23,820
I'm Jeong Hee Wan.

47
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,130
I'm in a hurry right now.

48
00:03:25,130 --> 00:03:27,240
The drug you prescribed to me.

49
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:29,750
Is hallucination one of the side effects?

50
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,870
It is, right?

51
00:03:31,870 --> 00:03:33,550
You checked all the pills, right?

52
00:03:33,550 --> 00:03:39,040
Yes, it usually takes a few hours to accept.

53
00:03:39,720 --> 00:03:43,320
But you'll regret wasting time like this later.

54
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:46,230
You regret so many things after you die.

55
00:03:46,230 --> 00:03:49,010
Let me give you a piece of advice.

56
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:54,670
♫  The Bodhisattva of Compassion  ♫

57
00:03:54,670 --> 00:03:57,810
♫  When he meditated deeply  ♫

58
00:03:57,810 --> 00:04:00,070
Excuse me.

59
00:04:00,070 --> 00:04:02,520
Excuse me.

60
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,040
I...

61
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,910
have years of experience.

62
00:04:05,910 --> 00:04:09,670
This is basically my work anthem now.

63
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,810
Have you come to your senses now?

64
00:04:14,810 --> 00:04:18,220
Let's clean the house first, then.

65
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:19,860
Look at these side dishes.

66
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:21,630
You didn't even touch them.

67
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:23,960
Ahjussi and Hee Joo would be so upset

68
00:04:23,960 --> 00:04:26,250
to see this after you die.

69
00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:29,480
What are you, really?

70
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:31,430
What? I'm Hee Wan.

71
00:04:31,430 --> 00:04:32,740
Cut the crap.

72
00:04:32,740 --> 00:04:35,160
I'll flip out if you call me that again.

73
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:38,200
I'm Jeong Hee Wan and you're Kim Ram Woo.

74
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:40,200
I can't believe this. Hey.

75
00:04:40,200 --> 00:04:43,920
You're the one who insisted on switching names.

76
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:51,340
Wow, the yearbook. 
    

77
00:04:51,340 --> 00:04:53,240
They switched our names here.

78
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:55,530
We had to put stickers on each copy. Remember?

79
00:04:55,530 --> 00:04:57,600
We had cleaning duty for a month as punishment.

80
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:59,140
Here it is.

81
00:04:59,140 --> 00:05:02,250
It was so hard to stick these... 
    

82
00:05:02,250 --> 00:05:03,620
   

83
00:05:06,350 --> 00:05:08,330
Hey, Kim Ram Woo.

84
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:21,560
I had salt, chicken blood,

85
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:24,670
and all sorts of stuff thrown at me.

86
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,160
But a fire extinguisher...

87
00:05:30,160 --> 00:05:32,290
is a new one.

88
00:05:33,830 --> 00:05:35,980
 Hey, Kim Ram Woo. 

89
00:05:35,980 --> 00:05:38,640
- What? 
 - Do you know Bang Ji Soo?

90
00:05:38,640 --> 00:05:41,040
- Who? 
 - Bang Ji Soo from 10th grade.

91
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,100
She's looking for you.

92
00:05:43,830 --> 00:05:46,960
You know the hair treatment ad.

93
00:05:53,910 --> 00:05:57,920
Well, my handwriting is not good.

94
00:05:57,920 --> 00:06:00,940
I saw the letter you wrote for my friend.

95
00:06:00,940 --> 00:06:04,310
You made it look so pretty.

96
00:06:04,310 --> 00:06:06,630
The word must've spread all the way there.

97
00:06:06,630 --> 00:06:07,990
Is it a love letter?

98
00:06:07,990 --> 00:06:11,340
The pricing tiers are basic, premium,

99
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:13,940
special, and platinum.

100
00:06:13,940 --> 00:06:15,200
I choose the platinum.

101
00:06:15,200 --> 00:06:17,470
The platinum level is a bit pricy.

102
00:06:17,470 --> 00:06:19,930
- It's okay. 
 - It's 30,000 won.

103
00:06:19,930 --> 00:06:22,000
It's okay.

104
00:06:23,120 --> 00:06:25,050
A week is enough, right?

105
00:06:25,050 --> 00:06:27,470
I'm confessing my love in a week.

106
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:31,770
Our 100th day would be Christmas if we start dating then.

107
00:06:31,770 --> 00:06:35,660
I guess it's not possible that he'd say no.

108
00:06:35,660 --> 00:06:39,820
Well, no.

109
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:42,580
I brought the letter here.

110
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,210
"Your dizzying beauty."

111
00:06:46,210 --> 00:06:48,220
"The heart-wrenching smile"?

112
00:06:48,220 --> 00:06:50,890
Is there someone like this at our school?

113
00:06:50,890 --> 00:06:53,410
"I don't normally approach people first,"

114
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:56,800
"but you, Oppa Ram Woo, are an exception"?

115
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,310
Yes.

116
00:06:58,310 --> 00:07:00,470
It's Oppa Kim Ram Woo.

117
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,090
Not you, Unnie.

118
00:07:02,090 --> 00:07:05,780
Oppa Kim Ram Woo, who's called Jeong Hee Wan.

119
00:07:05,780 --> 00:07:07,930
Kim Ram Woo is the recipient of this letter?

120
00:07:07,930 --> 00:07:09,170
The Kim Ram Woo I know?

121
00:07:09,170 --> 00:07:11,270
Yes. Why?

122
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:13,210
Is that a problem?

123
00:07:13,210 --> 00:07:16,600
No, not at all. No problem.

124
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:20,370
But would Ram Woo like this stuff?

125
00:07:20,370 --> 00:07:22,110
I'm not really sure.

126
00:07:22,110 --> 00:07:23,450
Would he not?

127
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:25,410
Instead of doing this,

128
00:07:25,410 --> 00:07:28,560
should I just confess to his face?

129
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:31,310
No, no, no. The letter sounds good.

130
00:07:31,310 --> 00:07:33,410
The letter would be perfect.

131
00:07:33,410 --> 00:07:36,380
Writing is more expressive.

132
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:39,200
- I love it. 
 - Okay, then.

133
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:43,250
Here's the 30,000 won.

134
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:48,120
Hold on a second!

135
00:07:49,080 --> 00:07:52,050
Yes, Unnie. What is it?

136
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:57,010
There are modern, classic,

137
00:07:57,010 --> 00:07:58,950
petit, and lovely options.

138
00:07:58,950 --> 00:08:01,040
What would you like?

139
00:08:01,900 --> 00:08:04,420
Since you're closest to Oppa Ram Woo,

140
00:08:04,420 --> 00:08:06,960
choose the theme he'd like the most.

141
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,630
Fighting!

142
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:11,140
Fighting...

143
00:08:12,860 --> 00:08:14,660
Geez. 
    

144
00:08:14,660 --> 00:08:16,570
"Your dizzying beauty"?

145
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:20,040
She couldn't sleep thinking about him?

146
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:21,730
Quit drinking coffee.

147
00:08:21,730 --> 00:08:24,080
Darn.

148
00:08:30,350 --> 00:08:32,050
Darn it!

149
00:08:32,050 --> 00:08:34,080
Geez, so annoying!

150
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:36,390
   

151
00:08:42,380 --> 00:08:44,250
Kim Ram Woo.

152
00:08:49,260 --> 00:08:51,940
What's wrong? You look like a zombie.

153
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:53,380
What is it?

154
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:55,810
She's outside again.

155
00:08:55,810 --> 00:08:58,370
Bang Ji Soo? Is it Bang Ji Soo?

156
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:01,060
Just write it however.

157
00:09:01,060 --> 00:09:02,800
Hey, hey.

158
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,060
Tell her I'm sick.

159
00:09:04,060 --> 00:09:05,430
No, say I'm in the bathroom.

160
00:09:05,430 --> 00:09:06,700
No, no.

161
00:09:06,700 --> 00:09:09,590
Tell her I didn't come to school today, okay?

162
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:11,600
I can cover myself like this.

163
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:14,390
I'm not at school today. Okay?

164
00:09:20,340 --> 00:09:22,890
Please call Unnie for me.

165
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:26,630
She didn't come to school today.

166
00:09:26,630 --> 00:09:28,200
She's at the teachers' office.

167
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,240
She's at the infirmary.

168
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:30,930
She got into a traffic accident.

169
00:09:30,930 --> 00:09:32,390
She was hospitalized.

170
00:09:32,390 --> 00:09:34,590
- Unnie. 
 - If I...

171
00:09:34,590 --> 00:09:38,430
said she transferred, you won't believe it, right?

172
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:53,200
How long will you keep this up?

173
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:56,400
I feel sorry for you.

174
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,780
Just write it quickly and be done. What's this?

175
00:09:58,780 --> 00:10:00,880
It's the platinum level.

176
00:10:00,880 --> 00:10:03,640
But I can't come up with anything.

177
00:10:04,490 --> 00:10:07,900
Don't you think Ji Soo is all about her hair?

178
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:11,720
No, does the hair look good because it's her?

179
00:10:11,720 --> 00:10:14,150
Gosh, I'm going crazy.

180
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:17,100
Just confess your love to Jeong Hee Wan first.

181
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:18,370
What?

182
00:10:18,370 --> 00:10:21,700
What are you talking about? You're crazy.

183
00:10:21,700 --> 00:10:23,000
Stop dragging it.

184
00:10:23,000 --> 00:10:25,200
Get it off your chest and get dumped quickly.

185
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:26,770
The bigger the heartbreak is,

186
00:10:26,770 --> 00:10:28,430
the bigger the leap it brings to your life.

187
00:10:28,430 --> 00:10:30,860
Why? Look how singers make masterpieces after a breakup.

188
00:10:30,860 --> 00:10:32,380
Why are you being like this?

189
00:10:32,380 --> 00:10:33,780
Spit out your words now. 
  (T/N: Don't jinx it) 

190
00:10:33,780 --> 00:10:34,850
Spit them out.

191
00:10:34,850 --> 00:10:36,760
 Unnie! 

192
00:10:37,520 --> 00:10:40,650
- Hey, hey, hey. Finish the noodles. 
 - Go, go.

193
00:10:40,650 --> 00:10:41,710
- Go, go, go! 
 - Unnie, Unnie!

194
00:10:41,710 --> 00:10:43,560
- Go! 
 - Unnie, hold on. Unnie, Unnie!

195
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:46,560
- Hold on! Hold on! 
 - Go! Go!

196
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:15,600
She was right here.

197
00:11:22,660 --> 00:11:23,630
 Hey, hey! 

198
00:11:23,630 --> 00:11:25,320
What?

199
00:11:28,890 --> 00:11:31,400
Geez! Seriously!

200
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:34,920
Unnie?

201
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:40,200
Unnie?

202
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:00,350
 - Gosh. 
 - What class is she from? 

203
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:02,640
 - Did she really jump? 
 - What do we do? 

204
00:12:05,530 --> 00:12:08,310
Yes, this is Heewantang.

205
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:10,860
Suicide attempt?

206
00:12:10,860 --> 00:12:11,880
Dad!

207
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,500
I can't believe this.

208
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:17,030
She looked so cheerful and carefree when we saw her then.

209
00:12:17,030 --> 00:12:19,740
She still is totally carefree.

210
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:20,960
How could you say that?

211
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:25,870
I mean, she always does unbelievably weird things.

212
00:12:28,460 --> 00:12:30,640
You're so uncaring sometimes.

213
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:35,640
If you're struggling too much,

214
00:12:35,640 --> 00:12:39,560
you act bubbly so as not to let it show.

215
00:12:41,880 --> 00:12:44,050
Did Kim Ram Woo attempt suicide?

216
00:12:44,050 --> 00:12:45,330
Is she okay?

217
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:46,490
Did something happen to her?

218
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:47,900
I don't know either.

219
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:49,850
That's what I mean.

220
00:12:53,940 --> 00:12:58,080
 Let me know if I can help with anything. 

221
00:13:05,780 --> 00:13:08,190
She's gone crazy. Seriously.

222
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:12,120
I think she lost her mind.

223
00:13:14,140 --> 00:13:16,630
 Everyone really thought you lost your mind. 

224
00:13:16,630 --> 00:13:18,720
We were so worried.

225
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:19,880
But where are we going?

226
00:13:19,880 --> 00:13:22,120
What do you mean by "we"?

227
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:26,700
Whatever. I shouldn't react.

228
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,060
- Just accept it as it is. 
 - Seriously.

229
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:31,110
You aren't crazy.

230
00:13:31,110 --> 00:13:32,720
- I can't hear you. I can't hear you. 
 - I'm the Grim Reaper.

231
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,870
- I can't hear you! I can't hear you! 
 - Hey, hey. Look.

232
00:13:34,870 --> 00:13:38,170
I can't hear you. No, no, no...

233
00:13:38,900 --> 00:13:41,160
Welcome. 
    

234
00:13:41,160 --> 00:13:43,320
One adult, please.

235
00:13:44,240 --> 00:13:47,320
You're clever even at times like this.

236
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:09,940
 Hee Wan, do you still have that dream? 

237
00:14:09,940 --> 00:14:12,560
 The dream where your friend dies. 

238
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:14,950
 Is the person you see right now 

239
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:19,010
 the person from your dream? 

240
00:14:23,610 --> 00:14:26,880
Why are you so down after a bath?

241
00:14:28,730 --> 00:14:32,410
Gosh, I feel refreshed for the first time in a while, too.

242
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:33,650
My body felt stiff,

243
00:14:33,650 --> 00:14:36,470
but after the sauna, I feel alive.

244
00:14:36,470 --> 00:14:37,630
"Feel alive"?

245
00:14:37,630 --> 00:14:40,990
A weird thing for a dead person to say, right?

246
00:14:42,620 --> 00:14:44,890
Let's say I'll actually die.

247
00:14:44,890 --> 00:14:47,530
Why is it you, of all people, who's telling me that?

248
00:14:47,530 --> 00:14:49,560
Well...

249
00:14:51,590 --> 00:14:54,550
it's like calling in a favor from a friend.

250
00:14:54,550 --> 00:14:57,000
- Let's just say it's like that. 
 - A favor?

251
00:14:57,000 --> 00:14:59,590
Leave, then. I don't need you.

252
00:14:59,590 --> 00:15:02,010
Come back when I die.

253
00:15:07,230 --> 00:15:10,530
Hey, you can't just barge in...

254
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:15,030
- How long has it been? 
 - 18 every five minutes.

255
00:15:15,030 --> 00:15:17,220
Administering it.

256
00:15:22,340 --> 00:15:24,320
Assist.

257
00:15:24,320 --> 00:15:26,890
No shock. Switch now.

258
00:15:29,230 --> 00:15:31,210
It's a patient! Coming through!

259
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:32,510
Excuse me.

260
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:35,200
- Get him a GS operation room. 
 - Okay.

261
00:15:47,830 --> 00:15:50,580
It's dropping. It's 40 now.

262
00:15:50,580 --> 00:15:52,350
Doctor.

263
00:15:56,290 --> 00:15:57,950
Let's stop.

264
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:02,030
Time of death, 4:55 p.m.

265
00:16:05,040 --> 00:16:07,660
Mr. Im Soo Hyeon, you have passed away.

266
00:16:08,620 --> 00:16:11,350
Born in the morning of October 12, 1991, between 11 am and 1 p.m.

267
00:16:11,350 --> 00:16:15,100
Died at 5 p.m. on April 1, 2024.

268
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:19,130
Im Soo Hyeon. Im Soo Hyeon. Im Soo Hyeon.

269
00:16:54,930 --> 00:16:56,710
